Dear Past Self, I know you're not ready for love or commitment right now, but this one is different. That beautiful woman in front of you, she's about to bring an overabundance of joy and happiness into your life in a way that you could never imagine. 

You may not have much more to give her than what's on that table, but what you do give her, she will multiply. 

You give her a house, and she'll turn it into a home. 
You give her a ring, and she'll turn into a loving and devoted wife. 
You give her a baby, 3 to be exact, and she'll turn into an incredible mother who will nurture and care for your little ones with all the love in her heart.

You're about to embark on a journey with her that will be filled with ups and downs, but trust me, she's the one who will always be by your side, cheering you on, and making life worth living. So buckle up, buddy boy, because this woman is about to make your world a far better and brighter place. 

On this day, 2 years from now, you'll be getting married, and 7 years from now you'll be staying up way past your bedtime reminiscing on all the memories you've made together from the last 9 years, realizing how truly blessed your life has become because you followed your heart, and not your head.

p.s. Buy her flowers. Often. They don't have to be expensive, but they mean the absolute world to her.

Happy 7th anniversary, my love. I love you, far more than you will ever know.
 
#happyanniversary #wife #love #happyday
